# Windows Server Administration Lab

## Overview
Hands-on lab focused on Windows Server infrastructure, Active Directory, and network services.

## Key Tasks
- Installed and configured Domain Controller
- Managed Active Directory (Users, Groups, Organizational Units)
- Applied Group Policy (GPO)
- Configured DNS services
- Worked with basic security configurations and permissions

## Tools & Technologies
- Windows Server
- Active Directory
- Group Policy Management
- DNS

## Skills Demonstrated
- Windows Server administration
- Identity and access management
- Network services configuration
- Troubleshooting enterprise environments
